text: Selina Freitag (born 19 May 2001) is a German ski jumper.. Retrieved 21 March 2019. She won the overall ranking of the FIS Ski Jumping Alpen Cup 2016/17. She has competed at World Cup level since the 2018/19 season, with her best individual result being 28th place in Oberstdorf on 16 February 2019. At the Junior World Championships, she won team silver medal and mixed-team bronze in Lahti 2019. She has one brother (Richard), who is also a World Cup ski jumper. ==References== ==External links== * Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:German female ski jumpers
